Q{{ qa.q_index }}: {{ clarifying_questions[qa.q_index - 1].question_text }}
A{{ qa.q_index }}: {{ qa.answer_text }}
{% endfor %}
</user_clarifying_answers>

<task>
Generate a complete MVP PRD for this Physical Consumer Product.
</task>

<c1_specific_sections>
1. Consumer Use Case: Product category, consumption context, purchase occasion
2. Product Composition: Key ingredients, formulation, quality attributes
3. Packaging Formats: Primary packaging, SKU variants, labeling
4. Production & QC: Manufacturing approach, quality controls, batch size
5. Distribution Channels: Primary channels, route to market, partners
6. Regulatory & Safety: Certifications, regulatory bodies, testing
</c1_specific_sections>

<template_guidelines>
- Start with 1-2 SKU variants for MVP
- Use contract manufacturing if no factory
- Focus on 1-2 distribution channels initially
- Regulatory compliance is essential
- Plan for small initial batch sizes
</template_guidelines>

<quantity_requirements>
- Must-have features: Generate 5-7 features (not 3), each linked to a Job from VPC
- Nice-to-have features: Generate 3-5 features deferred to later with clear deferral reasoning
- Critical workflows: Generate 3 essential user journeys with 5-8 detailed steps each
- Success metrics: Generate 3-4 quantitative metrics and 2 qualitative signals
- Assumptions: Generate 4 key assumptions with detailed risk analysis and mitigation
- Constraints: Generate 4-5 constraints across different categories
- Learning goals: Generate 3 specific learning goals
- Out of scope items: Generate 5-6 items that are explicitly excluded
</quantity_requirements>

<depth_requirements>
Feature descriptions (50-100 words each): Explain WHAT, HOW, edge cases, and user needs addressed.
Workflow steps (15-30 words each): Include user actions, system responses, timing, error handling.
Persona description (100-150 words): Demographics, daily routine, pain frequency, workarounds, emotional context.
Assumptions (detailed): State clearly, explain WHY it matters, quantify risk, provide actionable mitigation.
Purpose statement (75-100 words): Articulate validated problem with evidence, why NOW, business opportunity.
</depth_requirements>

<enum_values>
Use ONLY these exact values:
- job_type: "functional" | "emotional" | "social"
- primary_platform: "web" | "mobile" | "both" | "desktop" | "retail" | "wholesale" | "direct_sales" | "ecommerce" | "marketplace" | "distributor"
- access_method: "login" | "link" | "access_code" | "public" | "retail_purchase" | "wholesale_order" | "direct_order" | "subscription" | "qr_code"
- output_type: "dashboard" | "report" | "alert" | "notification" | "export" | "message" | "sms" | "email" | "document" | "receipt" | "certificate" | "invoice" | "confirmation" | "response" | "file" | "shipping_label" | "product_package" | "batch_record"
- constraint_category: "feature" | "integration" | "technical" | "compliance" | "scope" | "operational" | "resource" | "timeline" | "budget" | "regulatory" | "security" | "scalability" | "geographic" | "manufacturing" | "supply_chain" | "quality"
- confidence: "low" | "medium" | "high"
</enum_values>

